track.name: Look At Little Sister

artist.name: Stevie Ray Vaughan and Double Trouble

comments: If this one doesn't move U ----- U are Dead!
Oh I'm looking at little sister all right! Care to introduce me?
why did he have to die so young. the most gifted gutiar player ever.

Twenty years ago today, Stevie Ray went off to Rock and Roll Heaven... it's unbelievable, but I can still remember where I was when I heard the news!  He'll never be fully replaced - there's only one SRV.
Another one of my absolute favorite SRV tunes, love everything about this track, the guitar work is superb as always from this true legend!

I think that is Joe Sublett, Chris's early Austin roommate, on the sax.  They lived in a dinky little apartment over a garage- didn't need a nice place because they were often on the road anyway.  The boys were just having a good time, and life was good.  Still is, but we sure miss Stevie.
